Post title: Error "Class 'core\cron' not found "
Post description: Hello, I use the mod_scheduler version 2023052400 on my 4.1.19 Moodle instance. In the schedule Task, the \mod_scheduler\task\send_reminders indicates error, and when I run manually the task I get the message: `Execute scheduled task: Send e-mail reminders for upcoming appointments (modscheduler\task\sendreminders) … started 13:58:12. Current memory use 2.7 MB. Debugging increased temporarily due to faildelay of 60 … used 1 dbqueries … used 0.0086491107940674 seconds Scheduled task failed: Send e-mail reminders for upcoming appointments (modscheduler\task\sendreminders),Class 'core\cron' not found Backtrace:` `line 263 of /lib/cronlib.php: call to modscheduler\task\sendreminders->execute()` `line 167 of /admin/cli/scheduledtask.php: call to cronruninnerscheduled_task()` Any ideas? Thanks and Best Regards, Florian
Comments associated with the post: 
Comment 1: Hi Florian, I encountered the same error and also this message while running tests on a current Moodle 5.0 build Deprecation: cron_setup_user has been deprecated since 4.2. Use \core\cron::setup_user() instead. See MDL-77837 for more information. some searching led me to https://github.com/open-lms-open-source/moodle-mod_hsuforum/issues/42 where mod_hsuforum gets fixed. Applying the same method (replacing all occurences of "cron_setup_user" with "\core\cron::setup_user") in /scheduler/classes/task/send_reminders.php I modified the last few lines of send_reminders.php to this and can now run the task again without errors: 
